                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> SPELDHURST and HARWARTON. Indenture made Christmas Day, <origDate notBefore="1518-04-22" notAfter="1519-04-21">10 Hen. VIII</origDate>, 
                  by which <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> 
                           <surname>Roston</surname>., LL.D., master</persName>, 
                  and the brethren of <orgName key="org_109028">Corpus Christi College</orgName>, nigh the parish of
                  <placeName key="place_1083540">St. Lawrence Poultney, London</placeName>, demise unto
                  <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Waller</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_1083421">Growmbrigge (i.e. Groombridge) co. Kent</placeName>
                        </persName> 
                  their manors of <placeName type="manor" key="place_110012">Spelhurst</placeName> and 
                  <placeName type="manor" key="place_1083631">Harwarton</placeName>
                  for 20 years, at an annual rent of 56s. 8d.
                  
               </p>
